column8:
WINSTON -70s, English, tall, lean, well-
          dressed, glasses, tailored, precise

the DOCTOR -80s, steady hands,
          glasses, thinning hair, frail, but strong

EDDIE -30s, red beard, shaven head,
          pierced, tattooed, three piece suit

HARRY -60s, African-American, former NFL receiver,
          tall, lean, and imposing, yet currently dressed in boxers, a
          t-shirt, and dress shoes

the CAPTAIN -60s, enormous,
          grizzled, salt-and-pepper beard, long, unkempt hair, dressed
          in denim and leather

JOHN WICK -early sixties,
          salt-and-pepper hair, three-day beard, former boxer, former
          military, tired, beaten down, and at wit's end

an old, weary, and defeated
          soul

MARCUS -seventy, thin, balding,
          round spectacles, clean shaven, always well-dressed,
          expensive watch

DAVID PERKINS -late twenties, cocky, expensive tastes,
          lean, cruel

EDWARDO -58, nearing retirement, large, heavy,
          smarter than he looks

CARLO -late twenties, a bit dim, but nice
          enough

VIGGO TARASOV -60s, face
          scarred by a hard life, one eye dead, hair perfectly coifed,
          expensive suit, a slight limp, relying on a cane

VIKTOR -mid-twenties, short, stout, a pronounced LIMP,
          well-dressed, gawdy jewelry, terrible glasses

a single YOUNG DOG -a mutt of no distinguishable
          breed, three years old

a young, tri-colored (black, white, and brown),
          CHORGI (half-Corgi, half-Chihuahua)

JENNY -80s, African-American, petite, a commanding
          presence

IOSEF TARASOV -mid-twenties, thin, oiled hair, sunglasses,
          hipster, douche-bag

AURELIO -late sixties, hard eyes, soft
          smile, the father figure of this little family

CHARLIE -70s, small, creepy, thin, frail,
          eyes gentle, a tattooed smirk upon his lips

JIMMY -40s, African-American, three-piece suit,
          expensive watch, kind eyes, quick to smile
